|rad1chip2 = Ralink;; |rad1chip3 = |rad1oui = |rad1_ant_conn = RP-SMA |rad1stand = IEEE 802.11b |rad1b = 22 |rad1freq = 2.4 }}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== "103408600Y1" and "WPA400AM-Y1" is silkscreened on the mainboard. It is possible these units may have differing wireless modules (which do not appear to be standard PCMCIA). This particular one uses a [[National Datacomm NWH1021]]. The FCC photos depict the device with an RFMD based '''DBTel''' card, however, the FCC photos depict a different main board (probably for the A1 revision). The OUI of the MAC on the wireless module label is 00:80:C6 ('''[[National Datacomm]]'''). The OUI on the label affixed to the router is 00:0D:88 ('''[[D-Link]]''').
The RP-SMA antenna leads on the case exterior are soldered directly to the wireless module. ==Pictures==
